-- Kobe Bryant Passes Shaquille O’Neal for Fifth Place in NBA Career Scoring
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-02-07T01:11:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/kobe-bryant-passes-shaquille-o-neal-for-fifth-place-in-nba-career-scoring.html
Kobe Bryant  scored 24 points in the
first half of the  Los Angeles Lakers ’ game tonight at the
 Philadelphia 76ers , passing former teammate  Shaquille O’Neal  and
moving into fifth place on the career scoring list.  Bryant, who has 28,597 points after going 8-for-14 from the
field and hitting four 3-pointers in the first half, trails
 Kareem Abdul-Jabbar  (38,387 points),  Karl Malone  (36,928),
 Michael Jordan  (32,292) and Wilt Chamberlain (31,419) on the
National Basketball Association scoring list.  O’Neal had 28,596 points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  